        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 3:34PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northeast of Mulberry, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Cass...
Huntsville...                     Bidville...
Aurora...                         Crosses...
Combs...                          Turners Bend...
Cecil...                          Lonelm...
Georgetown...                     Boston...
Dutton...                         Mulberry...
Barnes...                         Pettigrew...
St. Paul...                       Redding...
Japton...                         Weathers...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 19 and
33.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
